============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Categorical Imperative
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Act only on principles you could will to be universal laws
Philosopher:  Immanuel Kant
Example:      Don't lie; if universal lying existed, language would break down

Concept:      Nihilism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Life has no inherent meaning; values are human inventions
Philosopher:  Nietzsche (diagnosed)
Example:      Without objective grounding, all moral frameworks are invented

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Boyle's Law
Formula: P₁V₁ = P₂V₂
Note:    Pressure and volume inversely proportional at constant T

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   E = mc²
Formula: E = mc²
Note:    Mass-energy equivalence; foundation of nuclear physics

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Planck's Constant
Formula: h = 6.626×10⁻³⁴ J·s
Note:    Quantum of action; E = hf for photon energy

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   DNA Structure
Formula: Double helix; A-T and G-C base pairs
Note:    Stores and transmits genetic information

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Natural Selection
Formula: Favorable traits lead to greater reproduction
Note:    Mechanism of evolution; Darwin 1859

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

Disease:     Cholera
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    Vibrio cholerae
Transmission:Contaminated water
Symptoms:    Profuse watery diarrhea, vomiting
Treatment:   Oral rehydration, antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   0.095M
Vaccine:     Yes
Discovered:  1854

Disease:     HIV/AIDS
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HIV
Transmission:Sexual contact, blood
Symptoms:    Flu-like; then AIDS symptoms
Treatment:   Antiretroviral therapy (ART)
Deaths/yr:   0.65M
Vaccine:     No (in development)
Discovered:  1983

